HEADWORD: Souari nut
<hw>Sou*a"ri nut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The large
edible nutlike seed of a tall tropical American tree (<spn>Caryocar
nuciferum</spn>) of the same natural order with the tea plant; -- also
called <altname>butternut</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>sawarra nut</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soubah</ent>⟦br⟧
